commitResults.messageTitle: Configure runtest.bat to correct input file
Relegate Task reading and writing to files
commitResults.messageBody:
Tasks are now written to a file on the computer
(or generated if not exist)

Users can fetch data after inputing their Tasks
rather than having it disappear

txt files are easy to write to and easy to read from
making them a good way enforce permanence in data.

commitResults.messageTitle: Specify Dates to be used in Deadline
commitResults.messageBody:
Deadline originally allowed any String to be set
as its /by value.

It is better to use an actual date so future filters
can search for deadlines and prioritise them

commitResults.messageTitle: Add Ui, TaskList, Storage, Parser classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Code logic was all placed in Tracker.java
This impedes new developers from understanding
what the Tracker's function is.

It is better to have a segregation of concerns
so that each feature is placed in its own classes

As such 4 new classes are made to accomodate
such functions

commitResults.messageTitle: Move classes to packages Main, Tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Besides relegating code logic to more classes
It is also good to move classes to packages
that clearly denote their functions

Additonal segregation of concerns thus added
Created a better environment for junit testing
